cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE

The paper proposes a deep learning approach for surface segmentation in medical images, specifically optical coherence tomography (OCT) images of retinas affected by age-related macular degeneration (AMD). This falls under computer vision (cs.CV) as well as machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of medical images also suggests a potential fit for multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the use of a convolutional neural network (CNN) for learning the surfaces suggests a potential fit for neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category.
